videos.description: A Florida defender goes underneath the screen, giving Aundre Jackson just enough space to drain a 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Jackson makes defender pay with 3-pointer

videos.description: Florida leaves Aundre Jackson open at the top of the key for his third 3-pointer in as many attempts.
videos.headline: Jackson drills third 3-pointer

videos.description: KeVaughn Allen knocks the ball loose and races to the other end for a two-handed jam.
videos.headline: Allen's intense defense leads to fast-break dunk

videos.description: Cameron Krutwig takes it strong to the basket, but Kevarrius Hayes swats his shot at the rim.
videos.headline: Hayes denies Krutwig at the rim

videos.description: Chris Chiozza catches defenders off-guard and throws a dime to Keith Stone on the baseline for a layup.
videos.headline: Chiozza throws sweet no-look pass

videos.description: Kevarrius Hayes intercepts the ball and throws down an emphatic one-handed dunk to give the Gators the lead for the first time since the beginning of the first half.
videos.headline: Hayes puts Florida ahead with thunderous dunk

videos.description: Cameron Satterwhite throws a lob to  Cameron Krutwig, who secures it and lays it in.
videos.headline: Krutwig makes alley-oop layup

videos.description: Chris Chiozza splits defenders and throws a sweet pass to KeVaughn Allen in the corner for a 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Hayes' block leads to open 3-pointer

videos.description: Kevarrius Hayes tips in the offensive rebound, but officials wave it off for offensive basket interference.
videos.headline: Florida's potential game-tying bucket waved off

videos.description: Dane Bradshaw says Florida failed to stop Loyola in the half court, while the Ramblers executed their game plan against the Gators.
videos.headline: Loyola-Chicago upsets No. 5 Florida
